Dixons Carphone plc is a multinational electrical and telecommunications retailer and services company headquartered in London, United Kingdom, formed on 7 August 2014 by the merger of Dixons Retail and Carphone Warehouse Group. It is listed on the London Stock Exchange and is a constituent of the FTSE 250 Index.
The company operates under a number of brands across the United Kingdom, Ireland and mainland Europe. These include Currys, PC World, Team Knowhow (previously Knowhow) and Carphone Warehouse in the United Kingdom; Currys PC World and Carphone Warehouse in the Republic of Ireland; PC World and Dixons Travel in airports in the United Kingdom; Elkj√∏p in the Nordic countries and Kotsovolos in Greece.


